    • Constructor Detail

      • MockFloor

        public MockFloor(SimRandom rand)
        Constructor of Mock Floor
        Parameters:
        rand - is a SimRandom for predictable randomness The logic of this Mock Floor is that the grid of locations in the warehouse is by (x,y) locations with (0,0) in the top left, and (width-1,depth-1) in the bottom right. The Point objects are used to refer to locations - methods anywhere just make a new Point(82,120) to refer to (82,120) for example. However, to know what is at a given (x,y), you need to look in the Cell for that point. Mock Floor therefore has a map from points to cells, the "allpoints" variable, which is the single authoritative place where cells are stored. All other parts of the warehouse need to call Floor methods to get a cell or store something in a cell.
